 Austria|Postal code]]\n| postal_code        = 9322\n| area_code_type = [[Telephone numbers in Austria|Area code]]\n| area_code      = 04268\n| website   = [http://www.micheldorf-hirt.at www.micheldorf-hirt.at]\n| footnotes = \n}}\n\n'''Micheldorf''' ({{lang-sl|Mihaelova vas}}) is a [[municipality]] in the district of [[Sankt Veit an der Glan (district)|Sankt Veit an der Glan]] in the [[Austria]]n state of [[Carinthia (state)|Carinthia]].\n\n==History==\nFirst mentioned in 1074 deed, it consists of the ''[[Katastralgemeinden]]'' Micheldorf and Lorenzenberg, which from 1973 until a 1992 [[referendum]] belonged to the neighbouring [[town]] of [[Friesach]]. Micheldorf also includes the village of Hirt, home of the Hirt [[brewery]].\n\n==Twin towns==\n*{{flagicon|Austria}} [[Micheldorf in Ober\u00f6sterreich]], [[Austria]] since 2002\n*{{flagicon|Italy}} [[Villesse]], [[Italy]] since 2003\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{commons|Micheldorf}}\n{{Cities and towns in Sankt Veit an der Glan (district)}}\n\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Sankt Veit an der Glan District]]\n\n{{Carinthia-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Micheldorf"}
{"title_page": "On the Wings of Love (TV series)", "text_new": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = On the Wings of Love\n| image                = Onthewingsoflove-titlecard.jpg\n| caption              =Title card\n| genre                = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Romance (love)|Romance]]\n* [[Comedy]]\n* [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]\n}}\n| creator              = {{Plainlist|\n* Dindo C. Perez\n* Reggie Amigo\n* Rondel P. Lindayag\n}}\n| creative_director    =\n| developer            = <!-- Add as a developer, creator, or concept for the series as spin-offs, remake, or adaptation -->\n| director             ={{Plainlist|\n* [[Antoinette Jadaone]]\n* Jojo A. Saguin\n* [[Dan Villegas]]\n* Darnel Villaflor\n* [[Francis Pasion]]\n}}\n| writer               = {{Plainlist|\n* Benedict Mique\n* Mariami Tanangco-Domingo\n* Nathaniel Arciaga\n* Allan Cuadra\n}}\n| executive_producer   = Arnel T. Nacario\n| producer             = Emerald C. Suarez\n| editor               = {{Plainlist|\n* Rommel Malimban\n* Bernie Diasanta\n}}\n| starring             = {{Plainlist|\n* [[James Reid (actor)|James Reid]]\n* [[Nadine Lustre]]\n}} \n| opentheme            = \"[[On the Wings of Love (song)|On the Wings of Love]]\" by [[Kyla]]<ref name=\"Kyla\">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5zg2988nl6M|title=\"On The Wings Of Love\" music video by Kyla|publisher=[[YouTube]]|work=ABSCBN Entertainment|date=May 16, 2015|accessdate=May 17, 2015|author=ABSCBN Entertainment}}</ref>\n| composer             = {{Plainlist|\n* Peter Schless\n* [[Jeffrey Osborne]]\n}}\n| country              = [[Philippines]]\n| language             = [[Filipino language|Filipino]], [[English language|English]]\n| location             = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Manila]], [[Philippines]]\n* [[San Francisco]], [[United States]]\n* [[Napa Valley]], United States\n* [[Talisay, Batangas]], Philippines\n* [[Ilocos Region|Ilocos]], Philippines\n* [[Lake Tahoe]], United States\n* [[Antipolo]], Philippines\n}}\n| cinematography       = {{Plainlist|\n* Hermann Claravall\n* Rodrigo Tinitigan\n}}\n| runtime              = 30\u201342&nbsp;minutes\n| network              = [[ABS-CBN (TV network)|ABS-CBN]]\n| company              = [[Dreamscape Entertainment Television]]\n| distributor          =\n| picture_format       = [[480i]] ([[SDTV]])<br />[[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2015|08|10}}\n| last_aired           = {{End date|2016|02|26}}\n| num_seasons          = \n| num_episodes         = 145\n| list_episodes        = List of On the Wings of Love episodes\n| related              = ''[[Till I Met You (TV series)|Till I Met You]]''\n| website              = http://onthewingsoflove.abs-cbn.com\n}}\n\n'''''On the Wings of Love''''' is a 2015 [[Republic of the Philippines|Philippine]] [[romantic comedy]] [[television series]] directed by [[Antoinette Jadaone]] and Jojo Saguin and starring [[James Reid (actor)|James Reid]] and [[Nadine Lustre]] in their first primetime television series. The series premiered on [[ABS-CBN (TV network)|ABS-CBN]]'s ''Primetime Bida'' evening block and worldwide on [[The Filipino Channel]] on August 10, 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abscbnpr.com/on-the-wings-of-love-arrives-on-abs-cbn-primetime-bida-this-monday/|title=\"ON THE WINGS OF LOVE\" ARRIVES ON ABS-CBN PRIMETIME BIDA THIS MONDAY|website=abscbnpr.com|date=August 4, 2015|accessdate=August 5, 2015}}</ref> replacing ''[[Bridges of Love]]'', and was replaced by ''[[The Story of Us (TV series)|The Story of Us]]''. <!-- Don't added grammar -->\n\nThe romantic comedy centers around two people \u2014 Clark, a boy living his American life and Leah, a simple girl with an American dream, who are forced to marry in order to legally stay and continue working in the United States.\n\nThe show ended on February 26, 2016 and this episode was divided into two parts: a recorded segment and followed by a live viewing party in [[Ynares Center]], [[Antipolo City]]. It was also simulcasted live on [[ABS-CBN (TV network)|ABS-CBN]] and worldwide on [[The Filipino Channel]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mb.com.ph/otwolthelastflight-reach-almost-4m-tweets/|title=#OTWOLTheLastFlight reach almost 4M tweets|newspaper=[[Manila Bulletin]]|date= February 27, 2016|accessdate=February 27, 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.philstar.com/entertainment/2016/02/27/1557348/photos-jadine-sweet-moments-otwol-finale|title=IN PHOTOS: JaDine sweet moments at \u2018OTWOL\u2019 finale|newspaper=[[Philippine Star]]|date= February 27, 2016|accessdate=February 27, 2016 }}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nLeah Olivar ([[Nadine Lustre]]) grew up in a very poor, but happy family. When she was 12 years old, her mother Rona (Isay Alvarez) goes to the United States to work for their family's better future. Life eventually becomes better for Leah, her sister, Tiffany ([[Bianca Manalo]]), and their father, Sol ([[Joel Torre]]). However, a tragedy changes their lives forever. For Leah, Rona's death creates a desire for her to go to the America and fulfill her mother's \"American dream\".\n\nTen years later, this dream comes true as Leah gets her visa to compete in a choir competition in San Francisco, California. After the contest, Leah extends her stay in San Francisco with the intention of visiting her mother's grave, and to find a way to legally work in the United States. However to her surprise, Leah does not find her mother's grave, and as her visa expires, finding a job that will allow her to remain in the United States also becomes elusive.\n\nWith the urging of Jack ([[Cherry Pie Picache]]), the mother of Leah's ex-boyfriend, Jigs ([[Albie Casi\u00f1o]]), and out of desperation, Leah agrees to a [[marriage of convenience]] so that she can get her visa. But with Leah's limited resources, it will be hard for Jack to find her a partner. The only suitable person that would agree to the small amount that Leah is willing to pay is Jack's nephew, Clark ([[James Reid (entertainer)|James Reid]]), who has been living in San Francisco for the past 11 years. His life has been full of heartbreaks as he went to the United States with his mother, Ofelia ([[Katya Santos]]), to be introduced to his American father, Kenneth. Soon after, Kenneth refuses to recognize Clark as his son, and Ofelia suddenly dies. Clark gets placed into foster homes, where he was abused. Later, because of his love for his siblings in the Philippines, Clark persevered and survived in the U.S. These misfortunes and responsibilities in life deprived Clark of romantic love.\n\nDespite their disastrous first meeting, Leah and Clark spend time as a fake couple and learn about each other's past, quirks and habits in order to pass the Immigration and Naturalization Service (INS) interview. As time passes, Leah and Clark discover a certain fondness for each other. They also realize that both have the same goals in life and that is to make a better life for their family.\n\nThey also start to sympathize with each other, as both reveal their deepest secrets. Soon, the sham marriage between Leah and Clark becomes real.\n\n== Cast and characters ==\n<!--Official cast billing from ABS-CBN.-->\n\n===Main cast ===\n<!--Do NOT create your own personal casting billing. Follow the opening credits. Starring credits are part of the Main cast; as for the 'Also starring' section it is for the supporting cast. Please do NOT change and put random characters in random casting sections. Thanks. Please do NOT change.--->\n* [[James Reid (entertainer)|James Reid]] as Clark Medina\n* [[Nadine Lustre]] as Leah Olivar-Medina\n<!---PICACHE, TORRE, INVENTOR, ALVAREZ, AND AVELINO ARE ALL PART OF THE MAIN CAST AS PER OPENING CREDITS. DO NOT CHANGE THIS.---><!-- Note: Paulo Avelino is credited as \"And In A Very Special Role\" in the opening credits. He is still part of the main cast, but is in a honorable mention. ---> \n* [[Cherry Pie Picache]] as Jacqueline \"Jack\" Fausto\n* [[Joel Torre]] as Soliman \"Sol\" Olivar\n* Nanette Inventor as Pacita \"Lola Pachang / Ima\" Magtoto-Fausto\n* Isay Alvarez<!---Please do NOT credited Isay Alvarez as \"Isay Alvarez-Se\u00f1a\". She is NOT credited in that name in the OPENING and ENDING credits so please do NOT credited her as this. Only credit and actor/actress as the way they are credited in the credits. Thanks. --> as Veronica \"Rona\" Martinez-Olivar / Wyatt\n\n===Very Special Role===\n* [[Paulo Avelino]] as Simon Evangelista<!-- Do NOT remove Paulo Avelino from the main cast. He is credited as a MAIN CAST character in the OPENING CREDITS. --->\n\n===Supporting cast ===\n* [[Albie Casi\u00f1o]] as Diego \"Jigs\" Fausto\n* [[Bianca Manalo]] as Tiffany Olivar-Carpio\n* [[Nico Antonio]] as Antonio \"Tolayts\" Carpio\n* [[Thou Reyes]] as Denzel<!-- Despite Thou Reyes' short appearance on the series, he was credited in the \"Also starring\" section. Do NOT put him in the guest stars section.--> \n* [[Jason Francisco]] as Cullen<!-- Please refrain from removing Jason Francisco from the SUPPORTING cast. He is CREDITED in the SUPPORTING CAST section in the OPENING CREDITS. Please do NOT put him in the Guest cast section because he is not a guest. --->\n<!-- The rest of the cast should be credited in the order the CREDITS credit them in the series. ---> \n* Paolo O'Hara as Abet Fausto\n* Jordan Castillo as Romer Fausto\n* Ruby Ruiz as Lolit Carpio\n* Joel Saracho as Mama Lulu\n* Geraldine Villamil as [[Punong Barangay|Kapitana]]\n* Juan Miguel Severo as Rico\n* Cheska Inigo as Diana Stevens\n* [[Kyle Echarri]] as Brent Wyatt\n* [[Ysabel Ortega]] as Angela Stevens-Fausto\n* [[Joseph Andre Garcia|Andre Garcia]] as Jordan Medina\n* Laiza Comia as Jennifer \"Jenny\" Medina\n* Nhikzy Calma as Gabriel \"Gabby\" Olivar-Carpio / Gabriel \"Gabby\" Velasco\n* Benj Manalo as Axl\n* Rafael \"Paeng\" Sudayan as Kiko\n* Jhustin Agustin as Rodolfo\n* Vivien Benjamin\n\n===Introducing===\n* [[Bailey May]] as Harry Fausto\n* [[Ylona Garcia]] as Audrey Olivar\n* [[Ynna Asistio]] as Maggie Regalado<!---Ynna Asistio was credited as a INTRODUCING along with the aforementioned characters. Please do NOT remove her and put her in the GUEST CAST section. Thanks.-->\n\n===Guest cast ===\n* [[Matt Evans]] as Adrian Velasco<!---Matt Evans is credited as \"Guest\" in the opening credits. Although he appears as a recurring character, he still a guest character and SHOULD NOT be place in the Supporting Cast section of the article. Please refrain from changing this. Thank you-->\n* Lee O'Brian as Arthur Wyatt\n* Miguel Faustmann as Kenneth<!--Do NOT put Kenneth's last name as \"Medina.\" It was not mentioned in the series-->\n* Anna Luna as Juliet Perez\n* Japo Parcero as Monette\n* Paul Cabral as Wedding Gown Designer\n* Mark McMahon as Ethan\n* James Vincent Martinez as Andres Suntay\n* [[Anne Curtis]] as Herself<!-- Anne Curtis was credited as a GUEST. Do NOT put her in the SPECIAL PARTICIPATION.-->\n* Jobelle Salvador as Flora Evangelista\n\n===Special participation ===\n* [[Katya Santos]] as Ofelia Fausto-Medina\n* Josh Ford as Young Clark Medina\n* Avery Balasbas as Young Leah Olivar\n* Trajan Moreno as Young Diego \"Jigs\" Fausto\n* [[Belle Mariano (actress)|Belle Mariano]] as Young Tiffany Olivar\n\n==Production==\n===Casting===\n''On the Wings of Love'' was the brainchild of [[Coco Martin]] based on his experiences as an OFW in [[Canada]]. The concept was originally supposed to be a movie starring Martin and superstar [[Nora Aunor]] but she turned down the role of Martin's mother as she was busy doing other projects.<ref name=\"casting\">{{cite news|url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/tv/23196/coco-martin-sarah-geronimo-were-supposed-to-play-clark-and-leah-in-emon-the-wings-of-loveem|title=Coco Martin, Sarah Geronimo were supposed to play Clark and Leah in On The Wings Of Love|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal|PEP]]|first=Nikko|last=Tuazon|date=March 1, 2016|accessdate=March 29, 2020}}</ref> The film would eventually be released in 2016 under the title ''[[Padre de Familia (film)|Padre de Familia]]''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Nora Aunor shares screen with Coco, Jasmine|url=http://entertainment.inquirer.net/129305/nora-aunor-shares-screen-with-coco-jasmine|publisher=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|date=January 12, 2014|accessdate=March 29, 2020|first=Bayani Jr.|last=San Diego}}</ref>\n\nWith the film's release then uncertain, the concept was turned into a teleserye which necessitated a change in the female lead to co-star with Martin. [[Judy Ann Santos]] was approached to be Martin's leading lady. Santos, however, turned down the offer due to unexpected pregnancy. [[Sarah Geronimo]] was also approached for the role of leading lady but also had to turn down the offer due to scheduling conflicts. Martin also ended up being busy with his teleserye, ''[[Ang Probinsyano]]''.<ref name=\"casting\"/>\n\nFinally, the roles were given to [[James Reid (entertainer)|James Reid]] and [[Nadine Lustre]] which marks their first lead roles in a teleserye as they signed exclusive contracts with [[ABS-CBN]].<ref name=\"casting\"/>\n\n===Soundtrack===\nIn March 2015, [[R&B]] singer [[Kyla]] recorded two cover versions of the series' [[On the Wings of Love (song)|eponymous theme song]] originally sung by [[Jeffrey Osborne]] and later covered by [[Regine Velasquez]]. The original version and its music video was released on May 16, 2015 via YouTube,<ref name=\"Kyla\"/> while the alternate version is a piano cover.\n\nThe theme song's original version is also part of the volume one of ''Dreamscape Televisions of Love'' album and Kyla's 15th anniversary compilation album ''My Very Best''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/323972039060/photos/a.10150344532044061.368557.323972039060/10153643227919061/?type=3&theater|title=The R&B Queen's 15th year Anniversary Album #MyVeryBest is NOW AVAILABLE!|author=[[PolyEast Records]]|publisher=[[Facebook]]|date=October 6, 2015|accessdate=January 19, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/ph/album/my-very-best-15th-anniversary/id1046721447|title=''My Very Best (15th Anniversary Album)'' by Kyla on iTunes|website=[[iTunes Store]]|publisher=[[Apple Inc.]]|location=Philippines|date=October 1, 2015|accessdate=January 19, 2016}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Artists\n!Song\n|-\n| Kyla\n| \"On the Wings of Love\"\n|-\n| James Reid and Nadine Lustre \n| \"On the Wings of Love\"\n|-\n| Erik Santos\n| \"Say You'll Never Go\"\n|-\n| James Reid and Nadine Lustre\n| \"Hanap-Hanap\"\n|-\n| Daryl Ong\n| \"Stay\"\n|-\n| James Reid\n| \"Randomantic\"\n|-\n| James Reid\n| \"Bonfire Love Song\"\n|-\n| James Reid\n| \"Babalik\"\n|-\n| Jed Madela\n| \"If You Don't Want To Fall\"\n|}\n\n==Reception==\n===Ratings===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"text-align:center; line-height:16px; width:100%;\"\n|+ KANTAR MEDIA NATIONAL TV RATINGS<br />(9:15PM PST)\n|-\n! PILOT EPISODE !! FINALE EPISODE !! PEAK !! AVERAGE !! SOURCE\n|-\n|| <center><span >'''22.1%'''</span></center>\n|| <center><span >'''27.8%'''</span></center>\n|| <center><span >'''27.8%'''</span></center>\n|| <center><span >'''20.9%'''</span></center>\n|| <ref name=psyreception>[http://abscbnpr.com/national-tv-ratings-urban-rural-may-22-25-2015/ NATIONAL TV RATINGS (Urban + Rural): May 22-25, 2015]. ''ABS-CBN Social Media Newsroom''. Retrieved 2015-05-26.</ref><ref>[http://abscbnpr.com/national-tv-ratings-17-22-august-2015-pangako-sayo-on-the-wings-of-love-and-ningning-hit-all-time-highs-in-tv-ratings-the-voice-kids-semi-finals-tops-saturday-programs/ National TV ratings (17-22 August 2015): Pangako Sa\u2019yo, On the Wings of Love, and Ningning hit all-time highs in TV ratings | The Voice Kids semi-finals tops Saturday programs]. ''ABS-CBN Social Media Newsroom''. Retrieved 2015-07-31.</ref>\n|}\n\n===Issues===\n====\"Dancing Police\" Scene====\nIn an episode, Clark (character of [[James Reid (entertainer)|James Reid]]) pretends to arrest, handcuff and blindfold his wife Leah (character of [[Nadine Lustre]]). Leah was shocked that her husband Clark was dancing while wearing a police uniform. Later on, a scene was made to show how they were sorry for making the police feel offended about the scene.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rappler.com/entertainment/news/121047-on-the-wings-of-love-otwol-police-uniform-controversy|title='On The Wings of Love' airs apology over police uniform controversy|publisher=[[Rappler]]|date=February 1, 2016|accessdate=March 29, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"text-align:center; line-height:18px; width:100%;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Association\n! Award\n! Category\n! style=\"width:200px;\"| Nominee\n! Result\n! Source\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2015\n| [[Star Cinema]]\n| 2015 StarCinema.com.ph Awards\n| Favorite TV Show\n| ''On the Wings of Love''\n| {{Won}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6BUegTODOjg|title=James Reid and Nadine Lustre win Favorite TV Love Team and TV show at the StarCinema com ph Award|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=November 10, 2015|accessdate=February 21, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Global City Innovative College]]\n| 1st GIC Innovation Awards for Television\n| Most Innovative TV Series\n| ''On the Wings of Love''\n| {{Won}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pep.ph/guide/tv/21936/aldub-hailed-as-most-innovative-tv-loveteam-eat-bulaga-otwol-chosen-as-most-innovative-shows-on-tele|title=Aldub hailed as Most Innovative TV Loveteam; Eat Bulaga, OTWOL chosen as Most Innovative shows on television|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|date=November 12, 2015|accessdate=February 21, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"17\" | 2016\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Guillermo Mendoza Memorial Scholarship Foundation\n| rowspan=\"2\" |  [[2016 GMMSF Box-Office Entertainment Awards|47th Box Office Entertainment Awards]]\n| Prince of Philippine Television\n| [[James Reid (entertainer)|James Reid]]\n| {{Won}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pep.ph